	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=22740&mid=108822757946829>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=22740&mid=108822757946829>Tactics</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=22740&mid=108822757946829#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Jun 26th 1:26 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=339797><span id= >Kanadr</span></a><br><span id=notbold>4 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I camped my burning embers the other day, without luck, and I just want to share my thoughts.&nbsp;&nbsp;Nezekezena pops much more than Phurz, and is much more difficult.  Our tactic was to use Slixx (the skele guy that drops the dirt of the underfoot just a skip away from the Phurz spawn point).  Bard charmed Slixx and used him to attack Nezekezena.  Awesome fight =).  Then you can kill Slixx and loot him and the wurm and maybe get 2 epic drops at the same time. Charms are awesome to use against this mob, just sit back and let your newfound pet die.  Nezekezena casted Ice Comet, AE Snare, AE Damage, and summoned me multiple times, also he was always red to me at level 48 (I saw him about 8 times).  Phurz only popped once in about 4-5 hours and I didn't notice any casting from him at all, but he fell very fast, and was yellow to me at level 48.  Also you want to have a guy permanently on add watch because they can make things much more painful in this area.  Me and a 65 warrior went back today to camp this item but could not find the wandering PH, bad luck I guess...  Hope this helps somebody.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
