	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=302413><span id= >DrJustice Esquire</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The exact hotspot is actually neg 470 neg 2550ish.&nbsp;&nbsp;You have to kill random trash mobs until you actually see just about any of the trash mobs spawn RIGHT ON that spot.  However, you better be ready to wait your arse off.  My guild went there with about 12 people, average raid level was 61.  After about 35-40 mins of killing everything in sight got the cycle started.  Once the cycle starts you can ignore everything but that spot.  Nez and Phurz both spawn right on the same spot as phs.  <br><br>Now for the bad news... maybe it was a bad streak, but we killed between 45-50 Nez's and Phurz's and got one Burning Embers drop.  While killing them wasnt too taxing for a group that size... you better be prepared for some serious frustration (like almost every single piece of mage epic).  It averages about 7 or 8 phs in between each Nez or Phurz spawn.  However it is streaky.  Sometimes they will spawn every other pop... sometimes will take upwards of 15 or so phs.  For any bards reading this they drop the Red wurm gut about 66% of the time.  We left guts all over the place.<br><br>One last note, someone on these boards made some post like... &quot;I solod Nez at 52&quot;  PFFFT doubt that Mr.  I tried a solo at lvl 54 with the Idea of chain petting him.  Better get over that idea.  As soon as I drop my pet with just a sliver of reconjure time left before my new pet summon, he summoned me lickety split, interrupting my cast.  If you try to run he keeps summoning you over and over until you get lucky and he tries to nuke you.  At which point if you have Run3 you can then escape his range.  <br><br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Jun  6 03:06:40 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br>I drank what?<br></td></tr>
